cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and relation extraction from text. It also involves the use of neural networks for capturing compositional semantics of textual patterns. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques for knowledge base construction. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper involves the use of neural networks for learning embeddings and making predictions. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with extracting relations from text and building a knowledge base. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves the use of neural networks for learning embeddings and making predictions.
